  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Breakfast is buffet style with a selection of pastries, fresh fruit, cereals, yoghurt, cold cuts, cheeses and bread. Staying on half board plus you'll have dinner in the hotel restaurant with water and wine included. Upgrade to full board for breakfast, lunch and dinner. </p>
<p><strong>Sfera Restaurant</strong> is the hotel's main restaurant which serves delicious Apulian food. It's a lovely bright space on the ground floor in the hotel's largest dome.</p>
<p><strong>Globo Restaurant</strong> is the perfect choice if you're away with the children as they have a dedicated menu for them and a kids area to keep them entertained. The staff here are really welcoming, especially to the little ones. </p>
<p><strong>Terrace Sole &amp; Luna </strong>is upstairs on the first floor terrace of the main dome. Enjoy breakfast or dinner up here with panoramic sea views. This restaurant must be reserved and is available for a supplement which is payable locally.</p>
<p><strong>Bar Emiciclo</strong> is just beside the freshwater pool. It has a large shady terrace where you can enjoy drinks and snacks throughout the day. </p>
<p><strong>Bar Arcuato </strong>is located in between the sea water pool and the sun terrace near the sea, offering drinks and refreshments. </p>]]></cateringDescription>
