  <description><![CDATA[<p>Torre Cintola Natural Sea Emotions is in a fantastic location right on <a data-udi="umb://document/d0c28188245b40a396dd64fb346dffcd" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d0c28188245b40a396dd64fb346dffcd}" title="Puglia">Puglia</a>'s Adriatic Coast. It's known for its dome-shaped buildings that surround two large outdoor pools. The salt water pool is a bit shallower, which is ideal for little ones to splash about in. There's plenty of shaded sun loungers around to relax on too. Take a dip in the sea if you prefer, there’s a jetty over the rocks with steps into the water.</p>
<p>Some of the standard rooms are located in the smaller domes. They're perfect for couples, while others are in the main building and are a little more spacious making them great for families sharing a room.</p>
<p>The largest dome is the hotel's main restaurant where you'll have breakfast and dinner. We love the Apulian food here, especially the fresh fish. If you're after something special book a table upstairs at the Terrace Sole &amp; Luna Restaurant (supplement payable locally) - it has incredible sea views. </p>
<p>Hiring a car means you can get out and explore the stunning coastline and countryside villages. The fortified town of Monopoli is a must-see while you’re here and it’s only about six kilometres away.</p>
<p>Car hire is recommended for this hotel. Torre Cintola Natural Sea Emotions is approx. 50 mins from Bari or Brindisi airport.</p>]]></description>
